Package server.project

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ParsedElement
    A ParsedElement object represents any part of a ParsedProgram which can be translated to a string of source code.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ParsedAttribute
    A ParsedAttribute object represents a class member, i.e.
    ParsedClass
    A ParsedClass object represents a concrete type of a ParsedProgram.
    ParsedCustom
    A ParsedCustom object represents a block of code written by the user, which can be anything: an instruction, a class declaration...
    ParsedElse
    A ParsedElse object represents a set of instructions to be executed only if the condition of a ParsedIf doesn't hold.
    ParsedFor
    A ParsedFor object represents a set of instructions which has to be repeated a fixed number of times.
    ParsedIf
    A ParsedIf object represents a set of instructions which has to be executed only if a certain condition is satisfied.
    ParsedInstruction
    A ParsedInstruction object represents an instruction declared inside a ParsedMethod.
    ParsedInterface
    A ParsedInterface object represents a purely asbtract type of a ParsedProgram.
    ParsedMethod
    A ParsedMethod object represents an action which can be performed on the ParsedType which owns it.
    ParsedProgram
    A ParsedProgram object represents a set of ParsedTypes interacting with one another to form a software program.
    ParsedReturn
    A ParsedReturn object represents a statement of a ParsedMethod telling it to exit and return the control to the caller.
    ParsedStatement
    A ParsedStatement object is a ParsedInstruction representing an action to be performed on a specific variable.
    ParsedType
    A ParsedType object represents a type declared inside a ParsedProgram.
    ParsedWhile
    A ParsedWhile object represents a set of instructions which has to be repeated until a certain condition holds.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ParsedException
    A ParsedException object represents an exception which has occured when parsing a ParsedElement object.
